{"parse":{"title":"Mass operations of the NKVD","pageid":1182320,"revid":854072389,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"vertical-navbox nowraplinks hlist\" style=\"float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%;border-collapse: collapse;\"><tbody><tr><th style=\"padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em\">Mass repression in the Soviet Union</th></tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:#E9E9E9;padding:0.1em 0;;font-size:95%;\">\nEconomic repression</th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding:0 0.3em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Collectivization_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Collectivization in the Soviet Union\">Collectivization</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Dekulakization\" title=\"Dekulakization\">Dekulakization</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Soviet_famine_of_1932%E2%80%9333\" title=\"Soviet famine of 1932\u201333\">Soviet famine of 1932\u201333</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:#E9E9E9;padding:0.1em 0;;font-size:95%;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Political_repression_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Political repression in the Soviet Union\">Political repression</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding:0 0.3em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Red_Terror\" title=\"Red Terror\">Red Terror</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Great_Purge\" title=\"Great Purge\">Great Purge</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gulag\" title=\"Gulag\">Gulag</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Political_abuse_of_psychiatry_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Political abuse of psychiatry in the Soviet Union\">Psychiatric</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:#E9E9E9;padding:0.1em 0;;font-size:95%;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Ideological_repression_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Ideological repression in the Soviet Union\">Ideological repression</a></th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding:0 0.3em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Religion_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Religion in the Soviet Union\">Religion</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Anti-religious_campaign_during_the_Russian_Civil_War\" title=\"Anti-religious campaign during the Russian Civil War\">1917-1921</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/USSR_anti-religious_campaign_(1921%E2%80%9328)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USSR anti-religious campaign (1921\u201328)\">1921\u201328</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/USSR_anti-religious_campaign_(1928%E2%80%9341)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USSR anti-religious campaign (1928\u201341)\">1928\u201341</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/USSR_anti-religious_campaign_(1958%E2%80%9364)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USSR anti-religious campaign (1958\u201364)\">1958\u201364</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/USSR_anti-religious_campaign_(1970s%E2%80%9387)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USSR anti-religious campaign (1970s\u201387)\">1975\u201387</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Persecution_of_Christians_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Persecution of Christians in the Soviet Union\">Christianity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Islam_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Islam in the Soviet Union\">Islam</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Soviet_anti-religious_legislation\" title=\"Soviet anti-religious legislation\">Legislation</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Suppressed_research_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Suppressed research in the Soviet Union\">Science</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Censorship_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Censorship in the Soviet Union\">Censorship</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Censorship_of_images_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Censorship of images in the Soviet Union\">Images</a></li></ul></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><th style=\"padding:0.1em;background:#E9E9E9;padding:0.1em 0;;font-size:95%;\">\nEthnic repression</th></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding:0 0.3em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Antisemitism_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Antisemitism in the Soviet Union\">Antisemitism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Holodomor\" title=\"Holodomor\">Holodomor</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Polish_Operation_of_the_NKVD_(1937%E2%80%9338)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Polish Operation of the NKVD (1937\u201338)\">NKVD Polish Operation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Population_transfer_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Population transfer in the Soviet Union\">Population transfers</a></li></ul></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding:0 0.3em;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Repression_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Template:Repression in the Soviet Union\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Repression_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Template talk:Repression in the Soviet Union\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Repression_in_the_Soviet_Union&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Mass operations of the NKVD</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> were carried out during the <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Purge\" title=\"Great Purge\">Great Purge</a> and targeted specific categories of people. As a rule, they were carried out according to the corresponding order of the <a href=\"/wiki/People%27s_Commissar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"People&#39;s Commissar\">People's Commissar</a> of Internal Affairs <a href=\"/wiki/Nikolai_Yezhov\" title=\"Nikolai Yezhov\">Nikolai Yezhov</a>.\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Kulak\" title=\"Kulak\">Ex-kulaks, criminals, and other anti-Soviet elements</a> ~386,798 killed<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_no._00447\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order no. 00447\">NKVD Order no. 00447</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Traitor_of_Motherland_Family_Member\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Traitor of Motherland Family Member\">Traitor of Motherland Family Members</a>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_no._00486\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order no. 00486\">NKVD Order no. 00486</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kharbin_operation_of_the_NKVD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kharbin operation of the NKVD\">Kharbin operation of the NKVD</a> ~30,992 killed<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_no._00593\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order no. 00593\">NKVD Order no. 00593</a></li></ul></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"National_operations_of_the_NKVD\">National operations of the NKVD</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mass_operations_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: National operations of the NKVD\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The operations of this type in this period targeted \"foreign\" ethnicities (ethnicities with cross-border ties to foreign <a href=\"/wiki/Nation-states\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nation-states\">nation-states</a>), unlike <a href=\"/wiki/Population_transfer_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Population transfer in the Soviet Union\">nationally targeted repressions</a> during <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a>.\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Polish_Operation_of_the_NKVD\" title=\"Polish Operation of the NKVD\">Polish Operation of the NKVD</a> ~111,091 killed<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_%E2%84%96_00485\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order \u2116 00485\">NKVD Order \u2116 00485</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/German_Operation_of_the_NKVD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"German Operation of the NKVD\">German Operation of the NKVD</a> ~41,898 killed<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_%E2%84%96_00439\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order \u2116 00439\">NKVD Order \u2116 00439</a></li></ul></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Greek_Operation_of_NKVD\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Greek Operation of NKVD\">Greek Operation of NKVD</a> ~20,000<sup id=\"cite_ref-Greeks_of_the_Steppe_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Greeks_of_the_Steppe-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\u201450,000 <sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAgtzidis1991372\u2014382_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAgtzidis1991372\u2014382-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Latvian_Operation_of_the_NKVD\" title=\"Latvian Operation of the NKVD\">Latvian Operation of the NKVD</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Deportation_of_Koreans_in_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Deportation of Koreans in the Soviet Union\">Korean Operation of the NKVD</a> ~1/4 of the entire Soviet Korean population killed<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Romanian_Operation_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Romanian Operation of the NKVD (page does not exist)\">Romanian Operation of the NKVD</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Estonian_Operation_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Estonian Operation of the NKVD (page does not exist)\">Estonian Operation of the NKVD</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Finnish_Operation_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Finnish Operation of the NKVD (page does not exist)\">Finnish Operation of the NKVD</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rollback\">Rollback</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mass_operations_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Rollback\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>On November 17, 1938 a joint decree No. 81 of <a href=\"/wiki/Sovnarkom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sovnarkom\">Sovnarkom</a> <a href=\"/wiki/USSR\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"USSR\">USSR</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Central_Committee\" title=\"Central Committee\">Central Committee</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Communist_Party_of_the_Soviet_Union\" title=\"Communist Party of the Soviet Union\">Communist Party of the Soviet Union</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Decree_about_Arrests,_Prosecutor_Supervision_and_Course_of_Investigation\" title=\"Decree about Arrests, Prosecutor Supervision and Course of Investigation\">Decree about Arrests, Prosecutor Supervision and Course of Investigation</a> and the subsequent order of the NKVD undersigned by <a href=\"/wiki/Lavrentiy_Beria\" title=\"Lavrentiy Beria\">Lavrentiy Beria</a> cancelled most of NKVD orders of mass type (but not all, see, e.g., <a href=\"/wiki/NKVD_Order_no._00689\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NKVD Order no. 00689\">NKVD Order no. 00689</a>) and suspended implementation of death sentences, signifying the end of the <a href=\"/wiki/Great_Purge\" title=\"Great Purge\">Great Purge</a> (\"Yezhovshchina\").\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Mass_operations_of_the_NKVD&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Vadim_Rogovin\" title=\"Vadim Rogovin\">Vadim Rogovin</a> \"The Party of the Executed\" (1997) <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/5-85272-026-7\" title=\"Special:BookSources/5-85272-026-7\">5-85272-026-7</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://web.mit.edu/fjk/Public/Rogovin/volume5/i.html\">Chapter 1: \"Mass Operations\"</a> <span class=\"languageicon\">(in Russian)</span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Snyder, Timothy (2012). <i>Bloodlands: Europe Between Hitler and Stalin</i>. Basic Books. p.&#160;81. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0465002399\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0465002399\">978-0465002399</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Bloodlands%3A+Europe+Between+Hitler+and+Stalin&amp;rft.pages=81&amp;rft.pub=Basic+Books&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=978-0465002399&amp;rft.aulast=Snyder&amp;rft.aufirst=Timothy&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+operations+of+the+NKVD\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-news-from-elsewhere-28604779\">\"Ukraine: Secret service publishes Stalin files\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Ukraine%3A+Secret+service+publishes+Stalin+files&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fblogs-news-from-elsewhere-28604779&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+operations+of+the+NKVD\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Eric J. Schmaltz. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20111018085732/http://www.grhs.org/heritage/SovietRepression.pdf\">\"Soviet \"Paradise\" Revisited: Genocide, Dissent, Memory and Denial\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. GRHS Heritage Society. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.grhs.org/heritage/SovietRepression.pdf\">the original</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span> on October 18, 2011<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">April 26,</span> 2011</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Soviet+%22Paradise%22+Revisited%3A+Genocide%2C+Dissent%2C+Memory+and+Denial&amp;rft.pub=GRHS+Heritage+Society&amp;rft.au=Eric+J.+Schmaltz&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.grhs.org%2Fheritage%2FSovietRepression.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMass+operations+of+the+NKVD\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\u041d.\u041e\u0445\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043d, \u0410.\u0420\u043e\u0433\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439, \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0430. \u0418\u0437 \u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0438 \"\u043d\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0446\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u043f\